comment: Store hours Mon-Sat 9am-7pm. KARM is religiously oriented, but web searches turn up no connections between them and transphobia or homophobia

name: Grime doesn't pay coin laundry

comment: usually no staff working, just walk in and do your business

name: 1797 Hydraulic Road, Charlottesville, VA 22901, USA

comment: For anyone to use :-)

name: Target
directions: Directly to the right as you walk in the entrance. It's a "family restroom" located just before the gendered restrooms.

name: Piano Works (Second Floor)
directions: Main Entrance, take stairs to second floor, hang a right, walk to the furthest hallway, turn left, pass the Haritage Christion offices, then you'll see the two bathrooms.
comment: Follow the instructions on how to use them, because the doorways are all automatic.

name: Walmart Supercenter
directions: "Family Restroom" at the back of the store by the Site To Store counter. Gendered bathrooms on the left, single stall family restroom on the right.
comment: Surprisingly supportive for such a rual community. Management has removed people from the property for degrading or discriminating against anyone, LGBT included. If you feel uncomfortable there for any reason, ask to speak to management.

name: Supercuts Hair Salon
directions: It's straight back beyond the chairs, first door on the left.
comment: I don't know if you have to be a paying customer; I asked to use it before they knew I was picking someone up at the salon and they didn't question me.

name: San Francisco Art Institute
directions: The gender neutral bathrooms are right next to the Lecture Hall across from the cafe.

name: Berkeley Art Center
directions: The building is set back from the street and somewhat easy to miss. Situated right next to Live Oak Park, 20-30 minute walk from downtown Berkeley.
comment: Hours for this location are Wednesday - Sunday, 11am - 5pm. However, the gallery is often closed for installation so check berkeleyartcenter.org for the schedule.

name: The M Factor / Tillman Health Center
directions: Between Paisano and Overland. First floor
comment: open Tuesdays & Thursdays 2pm - 7pm

name: The M Factor
directions: Suite 105 inside the meeting room
comment: Open Tuesday and Thursday from 2:00pm-7:00pm.

name: Cascade UU Fellowship
directions: 2 restrooms, both adjacent to the Foyer.
comment: During office hours M,T,F 9am-3pm; W,Th 12pm-6pm; or by appointment.  www.cascadeuu.org

name: Compass Community Center
directions: Check in volunteer desk and the restrooms are in the hall to your left

name: First Unitarian Church of Albuquerque
directions: The restrooms in our Social Hall and the Memorial Hall across the courtyard from each other both have gender neutral restrooms (4 total.)
comment: Our buildings are unlocked on Sunday mornings only, but you may come to the office Monday - Thursday from 9:00 am until 4:00 pm and we will escort you to the closest gender neutral restroom. We are a liberal, welcoming community.

name: Nellis AFB Commissary
directions: At far end of store just past women's room
comment: On Nellis Air Force Base. This is an active US Air Force installation. Must have military ID/credentials to enter the base.

name: Buffalo wild wings

name: Chapman Medical Center
directions:
Leaving Lobby, make a right and then a left to find the single use locking bathrooms. Male
And female labeled, but private and single occupant use.

name: Unitarian Universalist Fellowship of Central Oregon
directions: The Family Restroom is located in the hall adjacent to the kitchen.
comment: The Family Restroom also has a shower.

name: Alcatraz Island
directions: There are two unisex (single stall) bathrooms on the island. One at the dock in the pavilion with the other bathrooms, and another right at the top of the hill just outside the main cell house (where the trams let people off).
comment: The whole island uses a septic system so everything smells really bad. Doesn't matter which bathroom you use.

name: Mom and Pop's
directions:
From the front door, just past the front counter there is a hallway to your right, with a men and women's single stall. 

From the back door, watch to your left for a hallway.

name: Coffee Hag
directions: Near the front counter

name: Best Buy
directions: Back left of the store behind the appliances before car installation bay. Down a short hallway.
comment: There are stalls in each restroom, store policy prevents discrimination on basis of gender identity or presentation. GM is good about equality, as are most associates or she will back you up. Still more public if you're not comfortable with it, but the business itself shouldn't give you any troubles.

name: Time Square Fish & Chips and Sports Bar
directions: In the back, behind the bar, gendered restrooms with multiple stalls, never an issue for Trans people to use restrooms here.

name: Saint Felix

name: Suzy Grace Electrolysis

name: James Reeb Unitarian Universalist Congregation

comment: During weekday business hours our front door may be locked. Come to the side door on 4th street and we will let you in. 608-242-8887

name: Boulder Valley Unitarian Universalist Fellowship
directions: This is an "L" shaped building, and the gender neutral restroom is halfway down the long end of the L and is clearly marked.
comment: This building is typically open Sundays 8:30 am to 1:30 pm, open on weekdays Mon/Tue/Wed/Fri 9 am to 4:30 pm, and open Thursdays on irregular schedule.

name: Boise Unitarian Universalist Fellowship
directions: off the north west and south entryways

name: First Unitarian Society of Ithaca
directions: take elevator to 2nd floor, restroom is off the main meeting room
comment: we have several restrooms that have been designated "gender neutral" due to a similar effort here in Ithaca - 3 more in the attached building  at 306 N Aurora St (non-accessible)

name: First Unitarian Society of Ithaca

comment: This is a very busy church and therefore our doors are often open during the week and during evenings.  All people are welcome at any time.
